# PanelContextual

Welcome to `PanelContextual` component.

We show customers a panel when they need to add items or information about items to a transaction. In trowsers, a panel can slide into place to help customers add items or information about items to a transaction.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/panel-contextual
```

```tsx
import { PanelContextual } from '@ids-ts/panel-contextual';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | Test automation ID |
| `placement` | `Placement` | No | Direction for the panel (Placement.Left, Placement.Right) |
| `open` | `boolean` | No | Whether the panel is opened or not |
| `showPanel` | `boolean` | No | [internal] The current Panel state |
| `hasCollapseControl` | `boolean` | No | Whether the panel is Collapsible or not |
| `onClose` | `React.ReactEventHandler<Element>` | No | Callback when component is closed/collapsed. |
| `onOpen` | `React.ReactEventHandler<Element>` | No | Callback when component is opened/expanded. |
| `children` | `React.ReactNode[] | React.ReactNode` | No | The children to be displayed within the Panel |
| `autoFocus` | `boolean` | No | If true, would put focus on first tabbable element inside panel after being opened |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface PanelContextualProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /** Test automation ID */
  automationId?: string;
  /** Direction for the panel (Placement.Left, Placement.Right) */
  placement?: Placement;
  /** Whether the panel is opened or not */
  open?: boolean;
  /** [internal] The current Panel state */
  showPanel?: boolean;
  /** Whether the panel is Collapsible or not */
  hasCollapseControl?: boolean;
  /** Callback when component is closed/collapsed. */
  onClose?: React.ReactEventHandler<Element>;
  /** Callback when component is opened/expanded. */
  onOpen?: React.ReactEventHandler<Element>;
  /** The children to be displayed within the Panel */
  children?: React.ReactNode[] | React.ReactNode;
  /** If true, would put focus on first tabbable element inside panel after being opened */
  autoFocus?: boolean;
}

export enum Placement {
  Left = 'left',
  Right = 'right'
}
```

</details>

